A clear example (scenario) below:

Assuming that the 3 HackerOne members have an administrator access:

@jobert = administrator
@rockyrobot = administrator
@philip = administrator

So even each one of you are administrator of HackerOne program:

@jobert will not be able to set the visibility of @philip and @rockyrobot , why ? because there is no option of that in https://hackerone.com/security/team_members

same thing with @philip and @rockyrobot , each of you will __NOT__ be able to change the public team visibility of each other's profile.

Only @jobert can set the visibility of the teams on __HIS OWN__ profile here: https://hackerone.com/settings/teams , unless @jobert will give his password to @philip and @rockyrobot :)

Hope the scenario above make sense.

Cheers
